members.biography:
Cecilia is a real estate professional based in the United Kingdom who manages clients from the South East Asian market, which includes Hong Kong, China, Singapore, Malaysia and Taiwan.

Cecilia can speak fluent Cantonese, Mandarin, and English. To succeed in the real estate industry, Cecilia excels at understanding her client’s needs and providing the best advice. Whether for a family searching for their dream home, luxury retirement property, holiday home or building up their property investment portfolio.

Before joining Victorstone, she was a Hong Kong and Singapore licensed Private Banker with over 20 years of experience in financial planning and private client advisory services at several international banks, including HSBC, Standard Chartered Bank, Bank of Singapore, ABN AMRO and China Constructure Bank Asia. Cecilia graduated from the University of Auckland, majoring in Finance and Statistics. Cecilia manages Asian clients, including Hong Kong, China, Taiwan, Singapore, Malaysia,  Australia, New Zealand and other Asia regions, in which the clients are Ultra High Net worth individuals and families.

Cecilia says:
“At Victorstone, we have forged strong relationships with many of the UK’s top developers, enabling me to offer my clients an enhanced choice.

Away from work, Cecilia likes spending time with their family. We love playing golf, cooking, and travelling are some of her passions. Cecilia married with two children, a boy and a girl.

After many years in the corporate world and running my businesses, I still love to help people who wish to do some good. I now enjoy taking on non-executive directorships or advisory boards. My first preference is not acting as a director but rather as an advisor.”

Fokrul is a highly experienced international residential and commercial estate agent professional with expertise in sourcing off-market opportunities within Central London on behalf of its partners and investors. He is also a founding member of the Victorstone group of companies.

An exceptional leader with strong values, Fokrul is an intelligent and articulate director who is always ready to assess, manage, and resolve problematic developments and situations. Drawing upon his strong analytical and critical thinking skills – and utilising his ability to maintain positive and trust-based relations with business partners, shareholders and authorities – he induces profitable growth and enables the company to flourish in every realm.

Fokrul was informally an advisory council member for the Guild Property Professionals and Relocation Agent Network part of Cartus. He was named Agent of the Year for the Guild Property Professionals for 2015, 2016, 2017 and 2018. Moreover, he was chosen Best Agent for Greater London by The Relocation Agent Network for 2015, 2016 and 2017. He is also the winner of the British Property Award winner for 2017, 2018, 2019, 2020 and 2021.

Over the years, Fokrul has partaken in a wide range of marathons and bike rides all over the world – raising money for charitable causes and helping communities which need it the most. Recently, he completed the 2022 London Marathon, raising a tremendous £1,500 for Able Child Africa.

During the course of 2022 and in the lead-up to the marathon, Fokrul overcame a long series of injuries and setbacks. 

Fokrul says:
“As a keen endurance runner and cyclist, I am always taking part in actions for calling, and charity for the greater good.

Outreach and charitable work are passions of mine, and my commitment to making a difference has supported me in a range of endeavours, including raising £10,000 for the Hands Across the Water Organization; over £3,000 for Macmillan Cancer by taking part in Brave the Shave; and supporting the humanitarian group Restless Being by raising more than £50,000 for this charity to date.

I also enjoy mentoring young upcoming individuals who have since gone on to be employed by multinational companies. Recently, I have been instrumental in training and mentoring international students from Insec Business School and the University of Normandy in France.

Away from work, I am a motivated and resilient family man who loves keeping fit and has an unwavering interest in ethics and diversity matters.”

Muhib heads Vctorstones residential property operation. Representing investors and developers alike.

Over the past two decades, Muhib has acquired extensive experience and knowledge in the sales industry. But he realised he had an entrepreneurial eye very early in life. Having worked both in the family business and by providing lunch services to staff faculty members at his secondary school, he has been self-sufficient since his early teens; in fact, by the time he sat his GCSEs, he was already enjoying an income of over £3,000 per month!

Being one of the Directors of Victorstone has allowed Muhib to run and expand the company’s various brands. While running our financial brokerage business, he successfully navigated the firm through a period of exponential growth via extensive branding and marketing; recruiting talented individuals; mentoring staff; growing the sales force; embarking upon mindset coaching; creating and implementing new products; creating and developing partnerships; promoting staff into senior roles, and consistently achieving revenue-based targets.

Muhib says:
“Even from a young age, I knew I had to elevate my skill sets and broaden my horizons. I firmly believe that my role as a door-to-door salesman really taught me to become thick-skinned, resilient, relentless, and tenacious in constantly striving to overachieve in every aspect of my working career.

I became a homeowner by 18 and then, in all honesty, became an accidental landlord.

Not realising yet that I had a passion for real estate, I delved into private and governmental sub-contracting recruitment. I spent over 6 years in this industry, which allowed me to express my sales skills whilst simultaneously assisting long-term unemployed people of all ages to re-enter the world of employment.

Growing up in an era where online recruitment agencies did not exist, I knew how difficult it was to secure employment. I took it upon myself as the branch manager to educate employers on the value of taking on long-term unemployed individuals from various age ranges, ad focusing on the merit of the individual, not necessarily the contents of their CV. It wasn’t an easy task, but it proved to be a great success, as my branch consistently achieved 110% of the target every month.

I took this initiative and decided to implement, train, coach and educate staff and management alike across our other sites to ensure that we had a consistent way of working but, more importantly, make sure the company achieved its financial targets, which allowed for the expansion onto upcoming new projects. This ultimately accelerated my growth and development and gave me my first experience at the director level.

Victorstone has truly benefited from working with apprenticeship companies and governmental-based recruitment agencies to help people from different walks of life harness their skills, find a career, and develop themselves through nurtured training and coaching as well as inner self-development with mindset coaching. We were once these young people trying to find ourselves, and today, we feel that it is our moral obligation to guide and support these individuals in finding a working path in life and providing a structured career progression within our business. Our success comes from our team!”

As a fellow founding member of the Victorstone group, Sofkul brings more than 20 years of experience in the real estate and financial services sectors into his role as Chief Executive Officer.

Uninspired by the prospect of working for somebody else for his entire career, he always believed he would eventually become an entrepreneur. After cutting his teeth at several prestigious companies, including the Royal Bank of Scotland and The Angel Group Plc, Sofkul eventually used his knowledge and experience to co-establish a unique property consultancy that is renowned as one of the most forward-thinking companies of its type, not only in London but overseas.   

With an impressive skill for creating and identifying business opportunities, Sofkul has been instrumental in driving our business forward. A naturally strategic thinker, he doesn’t let things happen – he makes things happen. And as a leader, he strives to inspire others; to motivate them towards achieving their own goals, which in turn can only yield wider benefits for the collective. He has an exceptional track record of building and developing world-class teams and has successfully built relationships and sourced investment opportunities for investors based in Hong Kong, Dubai, Riyadh and Doha developing win-win partnerships with proven longevity.

Sofkul has played a key part in helping Victorstone achieve global recognition for its work, including (but not limited to) accolades from the British Property Awards, the Guild of Property Professionals, and the Sunday Times Estate Agency of the Year Awards. Knowing that the real estate industry in the UK is at a crossroads – not least due to the pandemic, the resulting business landscape, and the rising influence of social media – he truly believes that embracing change and adapting the business accordingly is the only way forward.

Sofkul says:
“I am incredibly proud of the business we have built – particularly of the way our executive team has continued to invest in the development of our staff, and the international recognition this has brought us.
